<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<gpx creator="StravaGPX" version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1 http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1/gpx.xsd">
 <metadata>
  <name>Krygyzstan 1</name>
  <desc>0-17km: wooded valley, 2000m-2600m. 
Trees on one side of valley. 2 river crossings (first very well trodden, second same river but further upstream)

17km-34km: pass- 2600m-3800m-2600m
Rapidly above tree line, dont return til end. POtential for snow before pass. 4189 peak north side of pass. Can bail down valley from end.

34km-41km: wooded valley - 2600m-2800m
Below tree line - trees both sides. Immediate river crossing. Definitely been done before on heatmap.

41km-59km : pass - 2800m - 4200m - 2900m
Rapidly out of trees. Very steep mountains to south before pass. Valley leads to glacier. Steep climb to pass and steep off. Potential for snow.  4300m peak just south of pass. A little exposed after pass for 3km or so - then steep sided to north. Little heatmap evidence. Cross river early in valley. Few trees in  valley. Can bail down valley from end.

59km-71km : pass - 2900m -3500m - 2500m
Steep sided valley.  3950m peak just south of pass. Regain trees at 62km. Riverr crossing at some point in valley and larger one at end (well trodden). Can bail down valley at end.

71km-94km: Long valley, 2500m-3400m
Stay on north side of river. Some tree coverage but not consistent on that side of valley.

94km-123km: very wide valley - 3400m-3750m
Narrow initially past some lakes. Then increasingly wide / exposed. No trees. OPtional Peak at 104km.

</desc>
  <author>
   <name>Phil H</name>
   <link href="https://www.strava.com/athletes/39877123"/>
  </author>
  <copyright author="OpenStreetMap contributors">
